SuDK33JKLFZPAMUefm1ZT3uxP0juRylJAK4%2FvI3RVttV8byNzsWUC7oj8Blccb557zifn7hG2Q6tqnsn19dX0slT5T09KXdav4PBTRGU3PFnYrFxZ0ZHHvyWVYvzsyKsr69nKv9H1RR9FxU58AddI7Qh9pZa0Yf7Qu%2FObbcPuzC34%2FufDn%2FDglEgfm81ZvNBFclFs6Z%2FdL%2FkJd1f5Ce7u13e3%2B%2FNrbI8EffAtiu9weDAyVKG%2FCJW%2B6iGDtiizz%2BKzx%2F8D8Nlu3g%3D%3D" id="w1_2_5_6"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2ccc0;strokeColor=#c96a4a;fontColor=#5a2410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1076" y="271" width="251" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+7]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   265k lives-eq/$1k · 19% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Shrimp Welfare Project · 49%&lt;br&gt;▼ 191 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. Under RP medians a chicken&#x27;s welfare range is a third of a human&#x27;s, not a fiftieth, and wild/soil invertebrates carry significant aggregate (nematode) weight, so invertebrate work dominates. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 7 animals_matter_a_lot" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_7.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_7"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eec2a8;strokeColor=#c65a2e;fontColor=#5a2a10;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="864" y="542" width="323" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Suffering-focused&lt;br&gt;ethics&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   86k lives-eq/$1k · 47% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 34%&lt;br&gt;▼ 47 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Asymmetry: averting intense suffering takes priority over creating happiness. Factory farming, malaria and the worst wild-animal conditions weigh up; speculative future-flourishing bets weigh down. Arises most naturally from taking animal suffering seriously, so it requires animals_somewhat. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_8.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_8"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#e9b0a0;strokeColor=#b8402a;fontColor=#511810;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1017" y="813" width="244" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Resilience erodes&lt;br&gt;nuclear deterrence&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+11]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   265k lives-eq/$1k · 69% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 25%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + resilience_undermines_deterrence&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Peltzman effect for civil defence: making nuclear war survivable weakens deterrence and raises the chance of war, so a resilient-food dollar partly insures against a catastrophe it also makes marginally likelier. An alternative, lower estimate for ALLFED, anchored to Rodriguez&#x27;s ~0.4%/yr US-Russia war probability. Requires future people to be in the circle. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_11.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_11"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="987" y="1355" width="251" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Collapse reroll:&lt;br&gt;survivors rebuild wiser&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+12]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   265k lives-eq/$1k · 78% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 15%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + collapse_teaches_better_future&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Collapse-as-reroll, optimistic: survivors of a near-collapse rebuild wiser and more cautious, so much of the value of preventing a survivable collapse is recovered by the better rebuild — resilient-food work aimed at averting collapse is worth less. The opposite of collapse_degrades_future, so the two cannot be held together. Requires the undiscounted far future. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 12 collapse_teaches_better_future" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_12.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_12"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="987" y="1626" width="251" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Collapse reroll:&lt;br&gt;survivors stagnate&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+13]&lt;br&gt;→ ALLFED&lt;br&gt;   2385k lives-eq/$1k · 80% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up AI safety (Redwood Research) · 19%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + collapse_degrades_future&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Collapse-as-reroll, pessimistic: survivors become durably tech-averse and stagnate, locking in a permanently degraded future close in badness to extinction — so preventing a survivable collapse is worth much more, and resilient foods (ALLFED) can overtake AI safety. The opposite of collapse_teaches_better_future. Requires the undiscounted far future. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 13 collapse_degrades_future" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_13.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_13"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="298" y="1897" width="366" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Time of perils:&lt;br&gt;space settlement exits it&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+14]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   2878k lives-eq/$1k · 54% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 45%&lt;br&gt;(Toby Ord, Elon Musk)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + time_of_perils_exit&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Time-of-perils optimism: hazard is high during the AI / nuclear transition but collapses once decorrelated, self-sufficient settlements exist — no single catastrophe reaches them all. The window closes, the expected future stretches far past the background-hazard baseline, and x-risk reduction during the window is what unlocks it (Ord, The Precipice; the multiplanetary-backup argument). Mutually exclusive with the view that early expansion re-arms the hazard. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 14 time_of_perils_exit" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylWG1v2zgS%2FiuD4PbOzjmO5Hc7lwPSxtktLmmLJMViURcuLdE2N5KoI6ko3m72t9%2BQlGw6kRHj%2FKVV5OEzz7xwXvTjKKRzkkXqPQ%2Fp0ejo9BTOz8%2FhXhCWgOIQCPLHCh%2FyBCZZy%2FM7kHMRhY%2BM5pD709a0O%2B1N8W1NKp6C36nr45MEYS6kzOJUMZ5AsES0EXiQEsGDJSORBvOHLfBhTsSU5GQ1XWYxSWT5QwtIwmISyankMc2XRJW%2FdGGeqUzQ4sA0JkpRMc2ZWk5DJgOeJYoli1K8Bwl330%2B3Tq95dECxmE75fJpSwVAtfWLK2DEmwRLIxhgmgcDnlVri85xFFNBRm5%2FlKShNloShbICg6F2WUAlcGDBBT9AHJKZImUl8r5bUuucfEu1KAoNxBgGPUy61GWsBPJuEFBHxFZMGTSqShCTiCYUYwxc14fs6OuPH75qqPk6fUhooPPhIoowCnxuETSCbBuwdlQpm2QoyrUYflNQ1bAQXH0CSOVUrqN3SMOc8hFsUIiJY1i3Gz%2BOP49uL%2B%2FElzFawoAkVRNFmuipzh4ZMbTnrGH9sYISUpaT9iUgG60sSUKG04TEXmDFrv0kra51C0jRiVDbhbhU3I75IuMCsqf1Iuw1Ih93nusEyMRt6P8H7D2dGckYVsW9TwWdkxiKmkMiMa%2BNDnfhfvQb435pwRQLFUScR1EKhQKojkagGSA5UpwcXC4zf%2BGt%2BeXH92%2BnfvsGMRjzH3NZnTZzpEz5HKzyO2Ohbg4W6wyxQNiIYQ4oZiebbDL0schbO8ZaAlsaXJzpL4Z8QEEWkEjzFYzr%2Fk4yY5NQ5ScSJRSjiXbslsaSr0zv0XQJ%2FeT%2BdrgQ8SvjIRbgkmYS%2F%2FGZXvzxDRecYDCivCzrP3oYxXoYbLBJMO1ug0Ctvj6BlHD6CtvdcN3xlQCJ6kqWlees0LNgx%2B3pJ%2FiAihBwdiy4LIq7dReZIFmKrkiQYLbECSZWKaIyeh9onEaLHjTcQ3rI8g5AGXAgaEa1mI47uT%2FBvvE5IyHUdxuahXuTbJRNID%2Bh8rv9DRzqRTQXWImQww5Ses4DhcwPeja8%2B3Y5tdhqEnLLFUteYBuY4plbMtfITLFDBEvms%