lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+14+16+17]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   25 lives-eq/$1k · 3% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up The Humane League · 96%&lt;br&gt;(Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + time_of_perils_exit + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 14 time_of_perils_exit → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy9WGtP40gW%2FStXaGc3YUKw8056WYmGMNNa6G4BrdGoaaUrdiWpwXZ5q2xCpof%2B7XuqbCcOGHWkSPMFBbt877nnvuvbgc9nLA2SM%2Bnzg9HB8TGdnJzQrWIiokSSp9ifK%2FxYRnSXthy3Q0upAv9B8CUt3Ulr0p30Jm5n4uJvn2o6kTG5%2FboRchdB2KnWaRgnQkbkLSBzRA7FTElvIVhgRLrDFrk0Y2rClmw1WaQhi3TxokUsEiEL9ETLkC8XLCnedGmWJqni%2BQeTkCUJV5OlSBYTX2hPplEionlxvEeRLD%2BfbH29xtGhRIR8ImeTmCsBtfxRrFW6PQrEg%2FlYRBMtwjRg1q7idZ%2FwkZbRhM1m3LNaDE2WhjHzFsQ2XAhNjD6ukgV%2Bz0TACWxvXutjSoytzPd1gxSHi0TENUllhSl%2BBApZyGGx0HieLHjG7r80aIk8K%2BMNeTKMpTYsrA%2Fg28jnkIhHQltpOmGRzwIZcQoRA0GTvq5dPH74aqCaz%2FljDKPw4QMLUk5yZiVsoqFphb3lOqFpuqLUqDEfal42bESn70izGU9WVLvm%2FlJKn65xiClvUc9k%2FDJ%2BP74%2BvR2f03RFcx5xxRLejFdFAHIfPimTdYiXDTg4ySAZPiHJyvoUeVwlxvBQKgTcmjednc1IYXEcCK6bdLMKm4GcR1Ih6Grf4m6D4mH3qW5lWZ8NnZ%2Fo7N0be3LKE5Y9jZWcs